---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/CommonPage.astro'

const title = 'OpenClaw Weekly Usage Report'
const headings = [
  { depth: 2, slug: 'weekly-narrative', text: 'Weekly Narrative' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'daily-token-trend', text: 'Daily Token Trend' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'usage-breakdown', text: 'Usage Breakdown' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'top-sessions', text: 'Top Sessions' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'notes', text: 'Notes' }
]
---

<PageLayout title={title} {headings}>
  <div class='report-shell not-prose'>
    <p class='subtitle'>2026-04-05 to 2026-04-12 · local analytics built from OpenClaw session logs</p>

    <section class='glance-card'>
      <div class='glance-title'>At a glance</div>
      <p>
        This week OpenClaw was used mainly for code reading, with 1,416,919 total tokens across 4 sessions.
        The most-used tool was read, and cache reuse accounted for 87.5% of token volume, which suggests the
        workload was more iterative and orchestration-heavy than purely fresh prompting.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class='stats-grid'>
      <div class='stat-card'><div class='stat-value'>1,416,919</div><div class='stat-label'>Total Tokens</div></div>
      <div class='stat-card'><div class='stat-value'>4</div><div class='stat-label'>Sessions</div></div>
      <div class='stat-card'><div class='stat-value'>46</div><div class='stat-label'>Tool Calls</div></div>
      <div class='stat-card'><div class='stat-value'>87.5%</div><div class='stat-label'>Cache Share</div></div>
      <div class='stat-card'><div class='stat-value'>1</div><div class='stat-label'>Models Used</div></div>
      <div class='stat-card'><div class='stat-value'>$0.8592</div><div class='stat-label'>Logged Cost</div></div>
    </section>

    <h2 id='weekly-narrative'>Weekly Narrative</h2>
    <section class='copy-card'>
      <p>
        OpenClaw spent the week mostly acting like a code-reading and execution copilot. The total token volume
        looks large, but most of it came from cache reuse, which usually means ongoing iteration, tool-assisted
        workflows, and revisiting context instead of brute-force fresh prompting. In other words, this is a usage
        pattern closer to agent orchestration than just chatting.
      </p>
    </section>

    <h2 id='daily-token-trend'>Daily Token Trend</h2>
    <section class='chart-card'>
      <div class='bar-row'>
        <div class='bar-label'>2026-04-08</div>
        <div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill blue' style='width: 2.8%'></div></div>
        <div class='bar-value'>38,471</div>
      </div>
      <div class='bar-row'>
        <div class='bar-label'>2026-04-12</div>
        <div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill blue' style='width: 100%'></div></div>
        <div class='bar-value'>1,378,448</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <h2 id='usage-breakdown'>Usage Breakdown</h2>
    <div class='two-col'>
      <section class='chart-card'>
        <div class='section-label'>Top Tools Used</div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>read</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill cyan' style='width: 100%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>19</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>exec</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill cyan' style='width: 42.1%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>8</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>process</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill cyan' style='width: 31.6%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>6</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>update_plan</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill cyan' style='width: 26.3%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>5</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>write</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill cyan' style='width: 26.3%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>5</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>web_fetch</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill cyan' style='width: 15.8%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>3</div></div>
      </section>

      <section class='chart-card'>
        <div class='section-label'>Workload Mix</div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>Code Reading</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill green' style='width: 100%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>19</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>Other</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill green' style='width: 57.9%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>11</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>Automation</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill green' style='width: 42.1%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>8</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>Code Writing</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill green' style='width: 26.3%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>5</div></div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>Research</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill green' style='width: 15.8%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>3</div></div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class='two-col'>
      <section class='chart-card'>
        <div class='section-label'>Model Mix</div>
        <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>gpt-5.4</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill purple' style='width: 100%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>1,416,919</div></div>
      </section>

      <section class='chart-card'>
        <div class='section-label'>Reliability</div>
        <ul class='bullet-list'>
          <li>Tool calls: 46</li>
          <li>Logged tool/message errors: 0</li>
          <li>Cache reuse remained high, which usually points to efficient context carry-over.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>

    <h2 id='top-sessions'>Top Sessions</h2>
    <section class='chart-card'>
      <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>047833b3-317</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill amber' style='width: 100%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>1,226,462</div></div>
      <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>653c6d83-320</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill amber' style='width: 10.7%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>131,589</div></div>
      <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>d2f7f127-eab</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill amber' style='width: 3.1%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>38,471</div></div>
      <div class='bar-row'><div class='bar-label'>94141093-a2b</div><div class='bar-track'><div class='bar-fill amber' style='width: 1.7%'></div></div><div class='bar-value'>20,397</div></div>
    </section>

    <h2 id='notes'>Notes</h2>
    <section class='copy-card'>
      <p>
        This is a first public-facing prototype. The next obvious step is adding multi-week trend lines,
        better task categorization, and a more narrative “agent usage story” section so the page reads more
        like a product analytics artifact than a raw ops dashboard.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .report-shell {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .subtitle {
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
  }
  .glance-card,
  .stat-card,
  .chart-card,
  .copy-card {
    border: 1px solid rgb(var(--border));
    border-radius: 1rem;
    background: rgb(var(--background));
    box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04);
  }
  .glance-card {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08), rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.12));
  }
  .glance-title,
  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }
  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .stat-card {
    padding: 1.1rem 1rem;
  }
  .stat-value {
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: rgb(var(--foreground));
  }
  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .chart-card,
  .copy-card {
    padding: 1.15rem 1rem;
  }
  .bar-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }
  .bar-row:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .bar-label {
    width: 8.2rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    overflow: hidden;
    white-space: nowrap;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .bar-track {
    flex: 1;
    height: 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.18);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .bar-fill {
    height: 100%;
    border-radius: 999px;
  }
  .bar-fill.blue { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa); }
  .bar-fill.cyan { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #0891b2, #22d3ee); }
  .bar-fill.green { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #059669, #34d399); }
  .bar-fill.purple { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #a78bfa); }
  .bar-fill.amber { background: linear-gradient(90deg, #d97706, #fbbf24); }
  .bar-value {
    width: 5.75rem;
    text-align: right;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .bullet-list {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
  }
  .bullet-list li + li {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .stats-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
    .two-col {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
    .chart-card,
    .copy-card,
    .glance-card {
      padding: 1.35rem 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
